history.text: Hi there!
Hello.
Have you seen any good movies lately?
We'll be talking about Jaws, right?
I've actually seen Jaws recently
Oh really, did you enjoy the movie?  Can you tell me more about it?
I really did enjoy the movie. It's a classic for a reason, I feel. It was very thrilling and the sense of dread throughout was pretty palpable.
I usually don't like scary movies, would you consider it scary?
Parts of it are what I would consider very scary. Lots of blood and frightening moments.
What do you enjoy most about the movie?

I like the fact that it is a very big enemy that they must find and kill in revenge for attacking people on the beach. It's a very big mystery as to what the shark will do and if it is actually planning this or if it's just nature taking revenge on humanity.
It's a nail biter lol
There's no way of knowing how it will actually end and if they will actually kill the shark or be killed
So even though it is an older movie, it is still worth watching?
I am thinking of watching it.  And you do make it sound interesting.
Absolutely, the effects might be a little dated and not as believable as modern cgi but it still has a lot of impact
So you would recommend this movie to your friends?
Is there anything in the movie that you did not enjoy?

Absolutely, it's a great movie to watch when you want something thrilling or scary. Good movie night kind of movie. It has a bit of a slow buildup and it seems like they spend a lot of time on exposition and introduction but once they get out into water, they're in the shark's territory and it gets interesting.
That does sound like it might be worth watching.
Maybe I will have to go check it out this weekend.
It's great. It has a 97% on Rotten Tomatoes.
Wow, that's a really impressive score.
Yup, definitely a classic in cinema.
It seems like it would be really neat to watch this on the big screen.  I wonder if they show this at any theaters anymore these days.
Is there anything else you could tell me about the movie that I should know before watching it?
I bet they do on cult movie nights. It's directed by Steven Spielberg if that tells you anything, a very good director.
Oh yeah.  I have seen some other things he has done.  He is a pretty good director
Definitely, not everything he does is great but he's pretty consistent haha
Do you remember any of the other actors in Jaws?
There's Robert Shaw, Richard Dreyfuss, Roy Scheider and Lorraine Gary
Oh, I have heard of Richard Dreyfuss.  I like him
Definitely a good actor
Well, thank you for the recommendation.
No problem! It was nice chatting!

uid1response.feedback: They made it sound interesting and worth watching.
